    "title": "RPC not listening when starting up bitcoind with new ~/.bitcoin",
    "body": "On current master branch.\n\nSteps to recreate:\n\n1) run `bitcoind -daemon -debug`\n2) create the bitcoin.config file as requested\n\nOR\n\n1) copy a bitcoin.conf into ~/.bitcoin\n\n...\n\n3) start bitcoind with above parameters\n4) issue an RPC `stop` command \n\nResult is: `error: couldn't connect to server`\n\nServer killed, no mention of RPC upon inspecting the logs\n\nI've checked down to 33029bcedd982f80f7e380bff586f3ab644decce with no luck.\n\nInterestingly this is _not_ happening with `-testnet`\n\nA checkout of current master will reproduce the bug but can post logs if necessary.\n",
